blog.name: professor-orchid
blog.title: Headcanons & Science behind your Pokémon
blog.description: Has your Partner been acting weird lately? Do you need additional information about a certain species for a school research project? Have you observed some unnatural phenomenon? Ask this young and aspiring new pokemon researcher for his opinion! [Header by @autobottesla]

title: New Sobble Insights
body:
Ask Professor Orchid!

Hello, fellow Pokémon trainers and enthusiasts!
Chemical analysis of the water these Pokémon native to the Galar region use for their attacks has revealed a composition that is much closer to that of tears than the water that other water type Pokémon commonly use, which features much less organic compounds. Furthermore, just like with regular tears, that waters exact chemical composition changes drastically based on the mood that a Sobble is in while using an attack. Additional research is needed to see if the mood and the following composition of the resulting water type attack change the effect of the move in question.

summary: So today we had a very different day playing pokemon go! I got invited to join some of the most well known players of pokemon go...
body:
So today we had a very different day playing pokemon go! I got invited to join some of the most well known players of pokemon go in plymouth to do some raiding!

Instead of walking around, we used the ‘battle bus’ which was amazing, we hit a bunch of different raids and I completed a research task and found my second shiny aerodactyl!!
